---
title: 21 Day Aged Sirloin Steak with Mustard Crushed Potatoes, Spinach and Sun-Dried Tomato Butter
description: Nothing quite beats a sirloin steak pan-fried to perfection and paired with sides that accentuate its delicious rich flavour, and that’s how we know we have a winner with this recipe. Succulent steak works great with the tangy taste of mustard, which adds extra texture and bite to this recipe when stirred through the smashed potato side. To get the perfect steak, slice against the grain when cutting. Check the direction of the muscle fibres and cut against these for a steak that is tender and easy to chew.
